leads.lead_text: Seedling growth tips glaucous; fruits 4–6 mm diam.; Wail State Forest
Seedling growth tips green; fruits 5–9 mm diam.; widespread
Tree to 50 m tall; bark smooth, or rough on lower trunk for 2–6 m; buds and fruits usually in 3s; usually valleys and well-watered areas
Medium tree, usually to 15 m tall (sometimes to 40 m tall); bark rough over most of trunk; buds and fruits in 3s or 7s or a mixture of 3–7

Buds and fruits mainly in 7s, but sometimes fewer; rough bark extending to upper trunk or major branches; bark on lower trunk light grey; broadest adult leaves 3.5 cm wide; mainly south-western Victoria

Buds and fruits mainly in 3s, but occasionally more; rough bark extending to the secondary branches; bark on lower trunk blackish-brown; broadest adult leaves 2.5 cm wide; coastal plains mainly east of Port Phillip Bay
